===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|いん|yomi=kanon}}
The sense “shade” is from a {{der|ja|ltc|sort=いん|-}} reading of {{m|ltc|蔭}} which is reflected as modern Mandarin ''yīn''. This reading is not recorded in ''{{w|Guangyun}}'', but is found in ''{{w|Jiyun}}'' as the [[fanqie]] of {{ltc-l|於}} and {{ltc-l|金}}, and is the same as the original character {{ltc-l|陰}} (“shade” and a few other meanings).

The senses “shelter” and “benefit from ancestors” are from {{der|ja|ltc|sort=いん|-}} {{ltc-l|蔭}}. Compare modern Mandarin ''yìn''.

The ''[[漢音#Japanese|kan'on]]'' pronunciation, so likely a later borrowing.

